# Copy to .env.local and fill in once your Swiggy Builders Club application
# is approved (https://mcp.swiggy.com/builders/access/).
#
# Without this token, the app runs in mock mode using a curated catalog —
# every UI flow still works, badges read "Demo data". Set the token and the
# same routes start hitting mcp.swiggy.com/food for live results, badges flip
# to "Live · Swiggy MCP".
#
# How to get the token:
#   1. Apply at mcp.swiggy.com/builders/access (Developer track).
#   2. After approval, complete the OAuth 2.1 PKCE flow:
#        client redirects to /authorize with PKCE challenge
#        user authenticates via phone + OTP in browser
#        client exchanges code + verifier for access_token
#   3. Paste the access_token below (without the "Bearer " prefix — the client
#      adds it).
SWIGGY_MCP_TOKEN=
